						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">At first it seems weird, you'd think it would be 2 times more complex to implement horizontal and vertical, but unfortunately no.</div><br />Yeah, it's more than twice as hard because one type of scrolling interferes with the other, which ends up complicating both of them. Making sure that both types of scrolling play nice with each other is not such a trivial thing. It's obviously not impossible either, it's just something you have to put a lot of thought into.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Also vertical scrolling is harder because of the incomplete attribute row at the end of each NES nametable.</div>
<br />That and because 30 (the number of tiles in a name table column) is not a power of 2. Attributes are definitely the worst part, though.</div>

